features: 📺TV WALL MOUNT：This is a universal TV mount for 32-75 inch flat/curved screen TVs from common major brands on the market with VESA support/mounting hole spacing from 45mmx45mm to 200x200mm, and a maximum weight capacity of 132 lbs. （Supports TVs up to 86 inches, just make sure the TV's VESA and weight requirements are met)

🎁FULL MOTION ADJUSTMENT: The range of motion of the TV wall mount bracket is quite large, you can rotate ±60° (max rotation depends on the size of your TV), adjust horizontal +/- 3°, tilt +5°/-15°, pull out to 15.2 inches or retract to 2.99 inches from the wall. Optimize your viewing experience wherever you are.

🛒ARTICULATING TV MOUNT：This wall mount TV bracket is designed with multi-functional double articulated arms, more sturdy and durable, easy to adjust, six-arm operation brings perfect viewing experience, and open wall plate provide more possibilities for mounting positions.

⏱EASY INSTALLATION: This full motion TV wall mount comes with all necessary screws and detailed instruction that is simple to install (especially for a non-technical person), only 15 mins to install this TV wall mount on 12" OR 16" wood studs or concrete/brick wall. DO NOT install it on drywall alone.

🥇10-YEAR FRIENDLY CUSTOMER SERVICE: As an enterprise focusing on TV wall mount brackets design innovation and production for 10 years, we have a professional after-sale team to offer you total solutions daily. If you have any questions, please feel free to contact us.

reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Very sturdy, stiff but does what it's supposed to do. Very impressed!
reviews.reviewText: Came with a guide to hang it and various screw lengths (although one was different from the rest, thank god I didn't need that size!). I'd make sure all of the correct parts and hardware is there before beginning, as that's been a big issue according to reviews I saw before purchasing, but I'm glad I did! I have a VERY expensive TV, and I'm glad I can trust this mount to hold it up. Very strong, swivel is great and extention is great too. I'd recommend not making the extention arms straighten completely out though, like i tried on day 1: the tilt on the tv loosened and my beloved tv fell forward, but caught safely, and nothing like that has happened like that again. Great mount!
